               <p>London Cases, Second Jury.</p>
               <p>Before Mr. Recorder.</p>
               <p>1573. 
               <persName id="t18250915-348-defend1756" type="defendantName">
                  MICHAEL 
                  BURKE
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-defend1756" type="surname" value="BURKE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-defend1756" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-defend1756" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for a <rs id="t18250915-348-off1881" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-off1881" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-off1881" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>
               misdemeanour
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>MESSRS. BOLLAND and LAW conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-348-victim1757" type="victimName">
                  ROBERT 
                  ABLETON
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1757" type="surname" value="ABLETON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1757" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1757" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18250915-348-viclabel1882" type="occupation">keep a chandler's-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-348-victim1757 t18250915-348-viclabel1882"></join> in <placeName id="t18250915-348-crimeloc1883">Fenchurch-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-348-crimeloc1883" type="placeName" value="Fenchurch-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-348-crimeloc1883" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-348-off1881 t18250915-348-crimeloc1883"></join>. On the <rs id="t18250915-348-cd1884" type="crimeDate">22d of August</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-348-off1881 t18250915-348-cd1884"></join>, about twelve o'clock in the morning, the prisoner came in and asked for a two-penny loaf - my wife served him - I was called from the parlour - he tendered a half crown, which I told him was bad, and he must know it - he said he would give me a good one - I said No - I beat it up with a hammer, and threw it into the street - he went out to pick it up, and threw it down the grating - he then returned and said he would have a good one for it, which I refused.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-348-victim1758" type="victimName">
                  THOMAS 
                  FARNELL
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1758" type="surname" value="FARNELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1758" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1758" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18250915-348-viclabel1885" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18250915-348-crimeloc1886">Horns public-house, Upper Thames-street</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-crimeloc1886" type="placeName" value="Horns public-house, Upper Thames-street"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-crimeloc1886" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-348-off1881 t18250915-348-crimeloc1886"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-348-victim1758 t18250915-348-viclabel1885"></join>. On the 22d of August, about ten or eleven in the morning, the prisoner came and had a glass of gin - he did not drink it, but took out half-a-crown, and laid it on the bar - I said it was bad - he said his eyes were very bad, and he could not see, but if I gave it him again he would give me another for it - I said No - I took out my knife, cut the letter T on it, and nailed it on the tap-room table - he wanted me to throw it down the kennel - Dady, the constable, called that evening, and I gave it to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-348-person1759">
                  SARAH 
                  CORNISH
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1759" type="surname" value="CORNISH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1759" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1759" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at the <placeName id="t18250915-348-crimeloc1887">Bull's Head public-house, Crescent, Jewin-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-348-crimeloc1887" type="placeName" value="Bull's Head public-house, Crescent, Jewin-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-348-crimeloc1887" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-348-off1881 t18250915-348-crimeloc1887"></join>, with my aunt - I am eleven years old. On the 23d of August, between three and four o'clock, the prisoner called for a pint of beer, and gave me half-a-crown, which I rung on the table, and called my aunt, as I thought it bad.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-348-person1760">
                  JOHN 
                  DINES
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1760" type="surname" value="DINES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1760" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1760" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Charter-house-lane. I was in the bar when the prisoner came in and paid this girl half-a-crown - she immediately sounded it on the table. I told her to call her aunt, saying I did not think it good. I afterwards cut it with the shears, and gave it to the officer - it is base metal - he wanted to go into the yard, but I would not let him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-348-victim1761" type="victimName">
                  SARAH 
                  TAYLOR
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1761" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1761" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-victim1761" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep the Bull's Head public-house. I found the prisoner at the bar-door - the bad half crown was given to me - the prisoner said he would give me another, and did so; I said he should not have the other till Dines cut it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-348-person1762">
                  RICHARD 
                  DADY
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1762" type="surname" value="DADY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1762" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1762" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. On the 22d of August Farnell gave me a half crown, which he had nailed to his counter.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-348-person1763">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PAYNE
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1763" type="surname" value="PAYNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1763" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1763" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am street-keeper of Barbican. I was fetched to Taylor's, and took the prisoner. I found a good half crown upon him in a bag, and 2 s. 7 d. in copper; Dines gave me a cut half crown.</p>
               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18250915-348-person1764">
                  JAMES 
                  FIELD
               <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1764" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1764" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-person1764" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am inspector of counterfeit coins; those half crowns are both bad, and from the same die, merely washed.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My eyes are very bad. I took them in the street for my oysters.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250915-348-verdict1888" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-348-verdict1888" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
